post_text: The creative minds behind @kamaelaskreamery shared their expertise with Elmwood High School’s young entrepreneurs. Kami and Mikaela talked a lot about the importance of community, and their willingness to share their time and talents were evidence that they truly believe in lifting others in our area toward success. post_text: Mrs. Davis’s 6th grade writers celebrated and shared their narrative writing today in a silent gallery walk. They invited other students, interns, teachers, and administrators to come read their work and leave feedback. Through their stories, they shared themes about hope, growth mindset, friendship, and love. Congratulations to our young authors and their teacher on publishing day! #trojanforce322 #elmwoodexcellence #youngauthor #writingcommunity

post_text: Our entrepreneurship students were so thankful to meet with local entrepreneur Paige Ehnle, owner of @norootsboots . Paige shared her enthusiasm for boots, business, storytelling, and connection while helping our students brainstorm ways to expand their already successful coffee cart. Students asked thoughtful questions and were so thankful for Paige’s willingness to share her experience on starting a mobile business from the ground up! #trojanforce322 #elmwoodexcellence
